   "It wasn’t the soft, patient kind of love people romanticize. It was sharp, expressive, always reaching, always asking. Her feelings didn’t sit gently between them—they filled the room, pressed against the walls, demanded to be seen, heard, acknowledged. For her, love meant intensity. If it wasn’t overwhelming, it wasn’t real.",
