   "But over time, that attention turned into something heavier.",
   "Every word he said began to carry weight he never intended. A delayed response became distance. A neutral reaction became rejection. Silence became a problem that needed solving. He found himself explaining things that didn’t need explanation, reassuring her for things he didn’t know he’d done.",
   "And slowly, without realizing it, he began to depend on her reactions to measure himself.",
   "If she was calm, he was okay.",
   "If she was upset, something must be wrong with him.",
   "That’s where the fear started.",
   "Not fear of her—but fear of failing her version of love.",
