   "“You’re not an easy person to love.”",
   "She believed it. To her, love required effort, constant proof, emotional investment that never switched off. And when he didn’t match that intensity, it felt like absence.",
   "But what she didn’t see was what those words were doing to him.",
   "He was trying.",
   "In ways she didn’t recognize. In ways that didn’t look loud or dramatic. He stayed. He listened. He adjusted. He absorbed her storms without walking away. But none of that seemed to count because it didn’t match her language of love.",
   "So he started questioning himself.",
   "Maybe he was hard to love.",
   "Maybe something in him was missing.",
